{
  "style": "",
  "texts": [
    "Concretely, the Toeplitz matrix is embedded in the top-left quadrant of the square (n + m -1) × (n + m -1) circulant matrix Equation (63): circ(y 0, y n+m-2, y n+m-3,..., y 1) = toep(y)• • •, (63)where circ(•) denotes the circulant matrix generating function as in Equation (24) and toep(y) denotes the Toeplitz matrix from Equation (33).",
    "Then, by padding the weak input x ∈ {0, 1} n with m -1 zeros (i.e., x → [x, {0} m-1]), the Toeplitz extractor can be recovered by the matrix-vector multiplication (circ(y 0, y n+m-2, y n+m-3,..., y 1)x ′) 0:m-1 where x ′ = [x, {0} m-1].",
    "Using this embedding, the Toeplitz extractor can be implemented using the NTT in O(n log n) computation time.",
    "The full implementation of the Toeplitz extractor can be seen in the pseudo-code in Algorithm 2.Total Computation Time: The Toeplitz extractor requires no pre-processing steps and can be computed by the convolution implemented using the NTT, embedding the Toeplitz matrix in a larger circulant matrix.",
    "This has total computation time O(n log n)."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}